Movie: I Now Pronounce You Chuck & Larry
Review: Feels like you can tell which scenes Alexander Payne wrote. Adam Sandler makes out with Jessica Biel to Radiohead at one point, really weird document.

The opening line for (Quicksilver Daydreams of) Maria is my favorite of any song I've heard, so I'm predisposed to loving this. Not to be an enabler (though I'm sure it would be the same the other way around), but some of the destructive drinks and hangs in this do seem fun.

Lots of great, entertaining anecdotes surrounding such an outstandingly captivating personally. But that brief tangent about an especially tired Blaze Foley sharing a quiet moment with his girlfriend -   performing If I Could Only Fly while they both cry - like come on I'm not made of stone.
A fully realized, idiosyncratic piece of feelbad vibes. Expected this to not land as well at home or show some worn elements, but this is at every minute hitting big swings out of the park
What the fuck do I even say here? Totally floored.
